osity of $698 \\,{\\rm fb}^{-1}$ containing $753 \\times\n10^{6}$ $B\\bar{B}$ pairs collected at the $\\Upsilon(4S)$ resonance with the\nBelle detector at the KEKB asymmetric-energy $e^{+}e^{-}$ collider. The\nbranching fraction is measured to be $\\mathcal{B}(B^{0} \\to \\eta \\eta ) =\n(7.6^{+2.7 +1.4}_{-2.3 -1.6}) \\times 10^{-7}$ at the level of 3.3 standard\ndeviations above zero, which provides the first evidence for the decay $B^{0}\n\\to \\eta \\eta$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2016 05:10:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-13"}
