of the\nequilibrium number has been taken into account. Comparing our theoretical\npredictions with experiments, it is shown the necessity of including the\ninstantaneous charge state and the BK charge distribution for a correct energy\nloss estimation. The results also show that the initial charge state has a\nstrong influence in order to estimate the energy loss of the uranium ions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2016 11:44:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-26"}
