e (alpha ~ 0.2-0.4)\nat all radii. The high-viscosity quiescent disc and the inferred low disc\ntemperatures in superoutburst are inconsistent with expectations of the\ndisc-instability model, and lead to the conclusion that the outbursts of V4140\nSgr are powered by mass transfer bursts from its donor star.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2016 15:46:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-21"}
